<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Index_CDS"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Index_CDS"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange Index Credit Default Swaps (Index CDSs, or
  CDXs).</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Index Credit Default Swaps</title>

    <para role="TEXT">Trades for indices, such as Index Credit Default Swaps, require the
    fewest data elements. Similar to a bond trade, the user selects the index,
    adds a notional, selects an index maturity tenor (5y, 10y), adds a deal
    spread and adds an upfront settlement amount.</para>
  </section>

